sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1065201
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Pxyl+GFP in an integrative Bacillus subtilis specific backbone
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The backbone comes from the LMU Munich IGEM 2012 team, the GFPmutB was extracted in pSB1A2 from the IGEM 2012 repository.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct is the composition of the Bacillus subtilis specific integrative backbone(BBa_K823024) with the biobrick BBa_E0840(strong RBS BBa_B0030 + GFP BBa_E0040 + terminators BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012).The backbone hosts the xylose inducible promoter Pxyl that control the expression of the GFP gene. The backbone is integrative for the locus thrC and gives different resistance according to the bacterial host:streptomicin in Bacillus subtilis, ampicillin in Escherichia coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Emil Tonon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pSBBs4S
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is an igem compatible version of the Bacillus expression vector pXT
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is an expression vector for Bacillus subtilis. It integrates at the thrC locus. It has a ampicillin resistance for cloning in E.coli and chloramphenicol resistance for selection in B.subtilis. The multiple cloning site downstream of a Pxyl promoter, that is inducible with xylose. This BioBrick is part of the LMU 2012 igem project Bacillus BioBrick Box http://2012.igem.org/Team:LMU-Munich/Bacillus_BioBricks
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We removed any forbidden restriction sites by site-directed mutagenesis PCR. The clonging site also includes a rfp for selection for cloning in E.coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jara Radeck

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
